  "summary": "Postinstall beacon executes host reconnaissance and outbound HTTP traffic",
  "details": "The package declares a postinstall lifecycle hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that runs automatically on npm install. Bundled alongside it are beacon24.js and beacon_linux.js, which import child_process, os, and http. beacon_linux.js reads os.hostname() and os.platform() and issues an outbound http.request POST carrying host identifiers; beacon24.js similarly combines child_process with HTTP GET traffic. This is the classic install-time host reconnaissance + exfiltration pattern: any developer or build system that runs `npm install event-metrics-q3x7` triggers spawned subprocesses and outbound network traffic carrying machine identity to an attacker-controlled endpoint, with no legitimate functionality matching the package name.",
